MBOMBELA – Eskom started implementing stage 2 load shedding from 17:00. This will continue until 21:00, the power utility announced in a statement. Some areas in Mbombela are likely to be without electricity on Saturday evening. According to City of Mbombela spokesman, Joseph Ngala, the following areas are likely to be affected from 19:00: ALSO READ: Load shedding commences in Mbombela Eskom has requested that users reduce their electricity consumption to relieve pressure on the power grid.